<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-494-540  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 494 540.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  May 21 1990 n591 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OTA: Rethink tech 'superiority'. (Office of Technology Assessment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>According to a report from the United States Office of TechnologyAssessment, the US may have to rethink its policy of maintainingstrategic technology superiority over enemies and allies alike.andO;The office points out that it is no longer possible for the US tolead in all or even most areas of technology, and cooperation withallies on technology issues is the only way for the US to maintainclose security alliances.andP;  The office warns that throughindustrial alliances, the US can avoid being left behind incertain areas.andP;  Thus, the US can avoid becoming dependent onforeign suppliers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Office of Technology AssessmentCooperationPolicyTechnologyMilitary.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>